Definition courte: Percentage of established calls over the requested ones for all types of connections. A call is established when the UE has established its E-Radio Access Bearer(s).
Definition longue: This KPI shows the eNB (radio part) observed probability to set up an end to end connection. Under the end to end a connection to be provided with an initial E RAB at request is meant. This KPI consists of two parts (phases): RRC and ERAB. Only initial ERAB setup attempts and successes are included in the KPI.

Definition courte: Percentage of ERAB Setups completed over the requested ones.
Definition longue: The KPI describes the setup success ratio of the elementary E-RAB setup procedure used to setup the E-RAB between MME and UE. It indicates the E-UTRAN contribution to network accessibility for the end-user, not the whole end-to-end service accessibility. This KPI can be used to evaluate the ERAB setup success rate of all services including the VoIP service in a cell or a cluster. This KPI is calculated based on the counters (both the ERAB setup attempts (All) and the successful ERAB setup (All) counters) measured at the eNodeB.

Definition courte: This KPI can be used to evaluate the performance of the network on the basis of the number of attempted handovers in reference to the number of established eRABs
Definition longue: This KPI describes the ratio of inter RAT handover attempts over successfully established eERABs.

Definition courte: This KPI can be used to evaluate the inter-RAT handover out success rate in a cell or a cluster. As suggested by the name  this KPI measures the performance of the inter-RAT handover from LTE to WCDMA.
Definition longue: This KPI describes the success ratio for the inter RAT handover execution phase  when the source eNB receives information that the UE successfully is connected to the target cell (WCDMA).

Definition courte: This KPI can be used to evaluate the inter-RAT handover success rate from LTE to GSM in a cell or a cluster for SRVCC.
Definition longue: This KPI can be used to evaluate the inter-RAT handover success rate from LTE to GSM in a cell or a cluster for SRVCC.

Definition courte: This KPI can be used to evaluate the inter-RAT handover success rate from LTE to WCDMA in a cell or a cluster for SRVCC.
Definition longue: This KPI can be used to evaluate the inter-RAT handover success rate from LTE to WCDMA in a cell or a cluster for SRVCC.

Definition courte: This KPI can be used to evaluate the intra-RAT handover success rate in a cell or a cluster.
Definition longue: This KPI describes the success ratio for the handover execution phase, when the source eNB receives information that the UE successfully is connected to the target cell within own eNB and for the inter eNB X2 and the inter eNB S1 based handover execution phase, when the source eNB receives information that the UE successfully is connected to the target cell within target eNB.

Aggregated DL Latency for a measurement period
Definition longue: Aggregated DL Latency for a measurement period. The effective DL Latency time comprises the time from PDCP DRB SDU entering the buffer until the first data has been transmitted to the UE. When carrier aggregation is used  the DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on the UE s primary component carrier (PCell). Condition: Measurement for UEs aggregated to cell level. Only PDCP SDUs that enters an empty buffer are measured. Samples during handover are excluded since they can distort the interpretation of the result (due to packet forwarding  the target cell might have to buffer data before it is possible to schedule the UE in the target cell  hence it would be an increased Latency measurement if it would be included. It would however not lead to a degraded performance for the end-user  due to packet forwarding).

For TDD  the UL is counted as possible time in micro sleep mode since the DU  during that time period  indicates no user data to transmit DL.

Definition courte: The total number of abnormal E-RAB Releases per cell initiated by the eNB and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).
Definition longue: The total number of abnormal E-RAB Releases per cell initiated by the eNB and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active). If there was data in the buffer at the time of release  then stepped at reception of S1 message E-RAB Release Command or UE Context Release Command when internal cause codes considered abnormal (Radio Connection with UE is lost  Handover failure for the UE  Non admitted E-RABs by target cell at successful handover for the UE  UE pre-emption) when the RBS initiated the release. It can also be stepped at transmission of E-RAB Release Indication  UE Context Release Request or Reset message by the RBS  or when a cell owned by that RBS is disabled (and that leads to internal RBS UE Context Release). In the UL case when a UE has multiple bearers co-existing and sharing the same LCG  the bearers share a single packet queue. If one of the bearers is released and there is data in the queue  the bearer s associated counter is incremented  regardless of whether or not the data belongs to the released bearer. Note. When the release cause indicates partial node restart  the actual status of the buffer is indeterminate at time of the restart therefore the bearer is instead considered active based on the latest RBS internal activity information (typically 1 second resolution)  meaning that a bearer counted as ""active"" could have been inactive for up to 1 second."
